    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with a high-floor offensive profile, anchored by **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (75.66) and **Gunnar Henderson** (75.35). **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** benefits from a favorable matchup against Simeon Woods Richardson, carrying an elite xwOBA of .389 that suggests he will anchor the run and RBI production despite a slight platoon disadvantage. Meanwhile, **Gunnar Henderson** remains a must-start; his leadoff role combined with a dynamic platoon edge against Will Warren creates a prime environment for both power and potential stolen base opportunities. While the starting rotation leans heavily on favorable matchups\u2014specifically targeting the inflated xERA of Christian Scott\u2014**Josh Lowe** (72.21) and **Nolan Schanuel** (64.63) are positioned to exploit that weak matchup, providing significant value for the bottom of our lineup. \n\nEfficiency gains today are largely driven by aggressive park and matchup adjustments. **Drake Baldwin** (72.68) and **Dominic Smith** (55.61) enjoy a massive park boost against Jose Quintana, whose 5.47 xERA is the softest target on the board. Similarly, **Miguel Vargas** (61.94) and **Heliot Ramos** (60.35) are bolstered by \"slow delivery\" metrics, which provide a nuanced, efficiency-based edge in the stolen base category, our scarcest resource. The most difficult benching decision involved **Josh Jung** (60.35); he missed the final lineup cut by a fraction of a point because the optimizer prioritized the specific platoon advantages of **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** and **Heliot Ramos**. While **Josh Jung** posted a strong score, the potential for **Heliot Ramos** to capitalize on a SB-friendly matchup against Shane McClanahan ultimately tilted the scale.\n\nWe remain at risk regarding the \"Lineup Pending\" status for several key contributors. All projections assume standard, historical batting orders, and any unexpected move to the bottom of the order for **Drake Baldwin** or **Jacob Wilson** would necessitate a recalculation of their respective lineup-position bonuses. Furthermore, while **Kyle Tucker** (72.04) and **Andy Pages** (65.61) are confirmed starters in the outfield, they face the left-handed Matthew Liberatore; despite the solid output, we will be monitoring the wind reports at the stadium, as a shift in direction could neutralize their power-heavy profiles. Keep a close eye on the official lineups to ensure **Jacob Wilson** and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** hold their projected spots, as those order-based multipliers are critical to their elite scoring output today.",
